name: Ganesha
description:
Although Ganesha has many attributes, 
he is readily identified by his elephant head. 
He is widely revered, more specifically, 
as the remover of obstacles; the patron of arts and sciences; 
and the deva of intellect and wisdom. As the god of beginnings, 
he is honoured at the start of rites and ceremonies. 
Ganesha is also invoked as patron of letters and learning during writing sessions. 
Several texts relate mythological anecdotes associated with his birth and exploits.
